ObAgent: uncertain.

Reason: multiple services show large drops in log.row_count and CPU (lower workload), while checkout latency-90 rises — consistent with either network-level packet loss (requests/packets dropped, surviving requests slow) or socket-level connection failures (errors causing failed requests and fewer logs). To disambiguate, check these metrics with whether_is_abnormal_metric:
- network.tcp.retransmits (or net.tcp.retrans_segs) — if high, indicates packet loss;
- net.if.rx_errors / tx_errors — indicates NIC-level loss;
- app.socket.connect_errors / socket.close_errors and service 5xx/error-rate — indicates socket errors;
- service request throughput/success_rate per endpoint (to confirm where traffic stopped).
If TCP retransmits are elevated, classify as network packet loss; if socket/connect errors spike without retransmits, classify as socket error.
JudgeAgent: No - Not found: agents only hypothesized network latency/packet loss but did not confirm required network KPIs (TCP retransmits/RTT/interface errors or socket error metrics) and did not uniquely select exactly one component as the root. Evidence shows multi-service trace/log row_count drops at 2024-01-18 03:04:00 and a checkoutservice latency-90 spike at 2024-01-18 03:21:00, so a single component/type/reason triplet was not pinned down.

